Sale Fares other rules and restrictions: All fares are one-way. All
fares are non-refundable, and a $50 per person fee applies to any
change made after purchase plus any applicable increase in airfare.
Travel on sale fares must be purchased no later than December 19,
2000.   All travel must be complete March 14, 2001.  Fares have a
7-day advance purchase restriction and may be combined with regular
fares to complete an itinerary.  Travel to/from Pittsburgh begins on
December 12, 2000.  Travel also may not be available to and from
select cities during other periods of high passenger demand such as
the Christmas, New Years, and President's Day holidays.  Seats are
limited and subject to availability.  Fares don't include segment
taxes of up to $2.75 for each segment.  A segment is defined as a
takeoff and landing.  Airport passenger facility charges of up to $12
are not included.


